        "text": "\n\nOLD WAY:\n- hosting servers do everything for you: mail, ftp, etc\n\nNEW WAY:\n- command line (example: digital ocean)\n   meaning you are not tied to their particular interface\n\nif they shut down their servers, you can easily move to another company\n\nThis is enabled thanks to a specific tool called Docker that enables you to deplopy any server here or there through your terminal anytime you want: so you are free.\n\nIt’s called: \nIndependant losely coupled servers   in technology\nfor ex: command line is losely coupled from one command to another (the command line is \n\n\nYou are not stuck in a culture\nYou have your own common tools with all the other tribes\n\n\nDISTRIBUTED:\nWhat enables you to be free is the Docker (which is like a virtual machine)+ it’s coupled storage for my own data (IPFS)\n\n\nWhy do they stay stuck in the past then, as they are smart people?\n- because of teenager images\n- Because of the emotional link to the things they built and that took them 3-4 years to build\n\nHow to collaborate with them then?\nOvercome resistence with an initial positive project, especially with their younger.\nFor instance, fed.wiki and IPFS, and micro-services (podcasting easily with 100s of other communities around the world)\nCCL: value through conversations with other federations worldwide."
