        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "d4e86888b264d34d",
        "text": "# The New Way of Hosting & Deploying\n**Hosting and deploying with the command line** (example: digital ocean).\nMeaning you are not tied to their particular interface, culture, language, or financial structure. \n\nFor example, if they shut down their servers overnight, you can easily move to another company. How?\n\nThis flexibility is enabled thanks to a specific tool called *Docker*, that lets you deplopy on any server here or there through your local terminal anytime you want to: then you are actually free.\n\nTechnically, it is called:**independant losely coupled servers**.\nFor example, the command line is loosely coupled from one command to another.\n\nSo from a tehcnological standpoint, what enables you to be free is both the Docker (which is like a virtual machine that simulated a server let's say) + IPFS which is its coupled storage for your own data (meaning you can store your data locally and quite easily have a p2p communication with any other machine in the world).\n\nAs a conclusion,\nYou cannot be stuck in a culture anymore,\nAnd you have your own common tools with all the other tribes.\n\n\n"
